	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">Does frequent writes/reads of battery backed RAM wear out anything? Use more juice? </div>
<br />If by juice you mean current from the battery, frequent writes/reads actually uses less because when the cart is in console and powered on the current comes from the console, not the battery. Note that this isn't significant however because the batteries are not rechargeable.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


