	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />In some of the GBA flash cards, the SRAM's "battery" is actually just a big capacitor so that the cart can be power cycled (GBA has no reset button) to write out the contents to flash.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


