	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">slobu wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">It sounds like, if I have the luxury, use some real RAM as a buffer and then back it up to save RAM only when needed. </div>This, except the opposite. There's literally no penalty to using on-cart SRAM, which is real RAM. Without having to double buffer memory your game will be faster and without waiting to flush data to the cart RAM a user has a better chance of their save surviving a random power loss.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
